# Dutch deck and declarative hands configuration

Full reference: `Documentation/Dutch_game/DECK_CREATION_RESHUFFLING_AND_CONFIG.md` (deck/reshuffle; paths there may say `cleco_game` — use `dutch_game` below).

Shared deal logic: `game_event_coordinator.dart` (Flutter + `dart_bkend_base_01` copies). Both use `DECK_CONFIG_PATH = 'assets/deck_config.yaml'` in `shared_imports.dart` but **resolve to different files per platform**.

## Config file map (edit the side that runs the match)

| Purpose | **Flutter** (practice, client-side match start) | **Dart backend** (WS server deals) |
|--------|--------------------------------------------------|--------------------------------------|
| Deck composition | `flutter_base_05/assets/deck_config.yaml` | `dart_bkend_base_01/lib/modules/dutch_game/config/deck_config.yaml` |
| Predefined hands | `flutter_base_05/assets/predefined_hands.yaml` | `dart_bkend_base_01/lib/modules/dutch_game/config/predefined_hands.yaml` |

**Keep both deck YAML files in sync** (ranks, points, powers, `demo_deck`, `deck_stats`). Predefined hands should match on both sides if server-hosted games use fixed deals.

There is **no** `backend_core/config/deck_config.yaml` on the backend anymore — only `lib/modules/dutch_game/config/`.

