## Predefined / declarative hands (`predefined_hands.yaml`) — both sides

```yaml
enabled: true          # false = random deal
hands:
  player_0:            # 0-based, exactly 4 cards
    - rank: "jack"
      suit: "hearts"
initial_discard:       # in YAML; not applied in coordinator yet
  rank: "ace"
  suit: "clubs"
```

### Behavior (same on Flutter and Dart backend)
- Deal at match start when `enabled: true`
- Pull cards by rank+suit from built deck; fallback random if not found
- All predefined ranks must exist in active deck or predefined hands disabled for entire deal
- `showInstructions` does not control predefined hands; deck choice does (demo vs standard/testing)
- Production APK: `playbooks/frontend/build_apk.sh` sets Flutter `enabled: false` — set backend `enabled: false` for production server too

---

## Reshuffling

Automatic in `dutch_game_round.dart` (Flutter + backend shared logic): discard pile except top → shuffled into draw pile (face-down). No YAML.

